{/* About Me Section */}

About Ava Smith

Frontend Developer

I am a passionate frontend developer with a knack for creating engaging, user-friendly web applications. With experience in HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and React, I strive to bring ideas to life through modern design and interactive interfaces.

{/* Education Section */}

Education

I hold a Bachelor's degree in Computer Science from the University of Tampa. During my studies, I focused on frontend development, web technologies, and interactive design. I also worked on numerous collaborative coding projects that honed my problem-solving skills.

{/* Experience Section */}

Experience

I have over three years of experience in building responsive websites and web applications. I have interned at several companies, where I collaborated with cross-functional teams to develop solutions for real-world business challenges. My projects range from e-commerce websites to interactive dashboards.

{/* Skills Section */}

Skills

My core skill set includes HTML, CSS, JavaScript, React, and version control systems like Git. I am also proficient in UI/UX design principles and accessibility standards. I enjoy learning new frameworks and am always seeking ways to improve the user experience through thoughtful design and coding practices.

); }; export default AboutMe;
